description:
Wire [watchdog] config section into SystemdWatchdog initialization.

The SystemdWatchdog in src/watchdog.rs auto-detects from env vars (WATCHDOG_USEC, NOTIFY_SOCKET).
After y17.1 adds WatchdogConfig to the schema, wire the config values as fallbacks.

CRITICAL SEQUENCING ISSUE: In main.rs, the watchdog is created at line 151 BEFORE config is
loaded at line 161. Must reorder initialization:
  1. Initialize logging (stays first — needed for config error messages)
  2. Load configuration (move BEFORE watchdog)
  3. Create watchdog with config values
  4. Start watchdog

New main.rs flow:
  let cli = Cli::parse();
  automated_flywheel_setup_checker::logging::init(cli.verbose);
  let config = load_config(cli.config.as_deref())?;   // ← moved UP
  let watchdog = if cli.watchdog {
      let wd = Arc::new(SystemdWatchdog::new().with_config(&config.watchdog));
      let _handle = wd.clone().start();
      Some(wd)
  } else {
      None
  };

Implementation on SystemdWatchdog:
1. Add log_pings: bool field to SystemdWatchdog (default false)
2. Add builder method:
   pub fn with_config(mut self, config: &WatchdogConfig) -> Self {
       // Config interval is a fallback: only use it if WATCHDOG_USEC was NOT set
       // (i.e., we're using the default 120s interval)
       if !self.enabled {
           // Not running under systemd — use config interval as the default
           self.interval = Duration::from_secs(config.default_interval_seconds);
       }
       self.log_pings = config.log_pings;
       self
   }
3. In the ping() method: use info! if log_pings else debug! (current behavior is always debug!)

Test:
- test_watchdog_with_config_override: create without env vars, apply config with interval=60s,
  verify interval is 60s
- test_watchdog_env_takes_priority: set WATCHDOG_USEC, apply config with different interval,
  verify WATCHDOG_USEC wins
